	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No, you are not biting off more than you can chew! I've always wanted to do something like this, but I am a little confused on some things too. Are you confused about scrolling? It's alot easier than it seems. There's like l00py's scrolling doc, and that is a peice, in my opinion anyway. It's really easy. I'm just going to give you an idea. Set up 2 variables (yscroll and xscroll), and do something like this:
<br />
<br />NMI:
<br />     lda xscroll
<br />     sta $2005   ;horizontal scroll register
<br />     lda #$00 
<br />     sta $2005   ;vertical scroll register
<br />     inc xscroll   ;increment scroll variable
<br />     inc vblcount ;increment vblank variable
<br />     rti
<br />
<br />You'd want to do this in your NMI, because it's done once per vblank, and yeah, I shouldn't be assuming you don't know this, I just know that l00py's doc will NOT help if you're a newbie, and GBAguy's tutorials don't explain it at all. But yes, I'd like to put together a document on things I didn't get when I was a newbie, like scrolling, attributes, sprite dma, and even simple math stuff, I was really bad at (see the 8 page object collision page). But yes, I'd really like this. We'll have to do it sometime! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

